official_title: A bill to designate certain lands in the Lake Woodruff National Wildlife Refuge, Lake and Volusia Counties, Fla., as wilderness.

summary.text: Designates approximately 1,106 acres in the Lake Woodruff National Wildlife Refuge, Lake Volusia Counties, Florida, as the Lake Woodruff Wilderness, to be administered by the Secretary of the Interior in accordance with the Wilderness Act, except that where appropriate, any reference in such Act to the Secretary of Agriculture shall be deemed to be a reference to the Secretary of the Interior.
